      ::Lord Jhiaxus::

Jhiaxus: Seems like we can just about get this show    on the road.

::Scorponok/Zarak::

Meanwhile, Zarak had    waited underground and Scorponok's internal repairs did their job. He had been    forced to flee the attack on that Maximal city but he had done far more damage    to them then vice versa.

Zarak decided it was time to locate his G2    Decepticon commander. He couldn't pick up a signature on his sensors    however.

Zarak: Where could you be on this rotten world,    Jhiaxus.

Zarak punches some controls and sends out a coded signal. It    would appear to be some kind of outdated stray Decepticon signal passing    through space unless decoded. It would take time for most subspace receivers    to pick up.
